Rivers State Commissioner for Information and Communications, Pastor Paulinus Nsirim, has debunked allegation by critics of Governor Nyesom Ezenwo Wike, that his administration is concentrating developmental projects only in Port Harcourt metropolis alone. Nsirim, who disclosed this while speaking in Port Harcourt, at a luncheon he organised for media executives and journalists in the state, said contrary to the impression being created, Wike has evenly spread developmental projects across all the local government areas of the state. He stated that the state has become a major player in national politics because of the vision and ingenuity of the governor towards rapid infrastructural development of the state. The commissioner further stated that the state has recorded giant strides under the Wike-led administration and charged the media in the state to shift its focus from the urban to the numerous rural developmental projects executed by the present administration.